#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.195"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.195:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.195:0.2"
msgid "20. Brāhmaṇavagga"
msgstr "20. Brahmins"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.195:0.3"
msgid "195. Piṅgiyānīsutta"
msgstr "195. Piṅgiyānī"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.195:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the "
"hall with the peaked roof."

msgctxt "an5.195:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena pañcamattāni licchavisatāni bhagavantaṃ payirupāsanti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time around five hundred Licchavis were visiting the Buddha."

msgctxt "an5.195:1.3"
msgid ""
"Appekacce licchavī nīlā honti nīlavaṇṇā nīlavatthā nīlālaṅkārā, appekacce "
"licchavī pītā honti pītavaṇṇā pītavatthā pītālaṅkārā, appekacce licchavī "
"lohitakā honti lohitakavaṇṇā lohitakavatthā lohitakālaṅkārā, appekacce "
"licchavī odātā honti odātavaṇṇā odātavatthā odātālaṅkārā."
msgstr ""
"Some of the Licchavis were in blue, of blue color, clad in blue, adorned "
"with blue. And some were similarly colored in yellow, red, or white."

msgctxt "an5.195:1.4"
msgid "Tyassudaṃ bhagavā atirocati vaṇṇena ceva yasasā ca."
msgstr "But the Buddha outshone them all in beauty and glory."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.195:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho piṅgiyānī brāhmaṇo uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena "
"bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the brahmin Piṅgīyānī got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one "
"shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said:"

msgctxt "an5.195:2.2"
msgid "“paṭibhāti maṃ, bhagavā, paṭibhāti maṃ, sugatā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I feel inspired to speak, Blessed One! I feel inspired to speak, Holy One!”"

msgctxt "an5.195:2.3"
msgid "“Paṭibhātu taṃ piṅgiyānī”ti bhagavā avoca."
msgstr "“Then speak as you feel inspired,” said the Buddha."

msgctxt "an5.195:2.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho piṅgiyānī brāhmaṇo bhagavato sammukhā sāruppāya gāthāya abhitthavi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the brahmin Piṅgīyānī extolled the Buddha in his presence with an "
"appropriate verse."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: Padmaṃ → padumaṃ (pts1, mr)
#. VAR: kokanadaṃ → kokanudaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an5.195:3.1"
msgid "“Padmaṃ yathā kokanadaṃ sugandhaṃ,"
msgstr "“Like a fragrant pink lotus"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.195:3.2"
msgid "Pāto siyā phullamavītagandhaṃ;"
msgstr "that blooms in the morning, its fragrance unfaded—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.195:3.3"
msgid "Aṅgīrasaṃ passa virocamānaṃ,"
msgstr "see Aṅgīrasa shine,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.195:3.4"
msgid "Tapantamādiccamivantalikkhe”ti."
msgstr "bright as the sun in the sky!”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.240"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.195:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te licchavī pañcahi uttarāsaṅgasatehi piṅgiyāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ "
"acchādesuṃ."
msgstr "Then those Licchavis clothed Piṅgiyānī with five hundred upper robes."

msgctxt "an5.195:4.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho piṅgiyānī brāhmaṇo tehi pañcahi uttarāsaṅgasatehi bhagavantaṃ "
"acchādesi."
msgstr "And Piṅgiyānī clothed the Buddha with them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.195:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā te licchavī etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the Licchavis:"

msgctxt "an5.195:5.2"
msgid "“pañcannaṃ, licchavī, ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "“Licchavis, the appearance of five treasures is rare in the world."

msgctxt "an5.195:5.3"
msgid "Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.195:5.4"
msgid "Tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "A Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha."

msgctxt "an5.195:5.5"
msgid "Tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desetā puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"A person who explains the teaching and training proclaimed by a Realized One."

msgctxt "an5.195:5.6"
msgid ""
"Tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desitassa viññātā puggalo dullabho "
"lokasmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"A person who understands the teaching and training proclaimed by a Realized "
"One."

msgctxt "an5.195:5.7"
msgid ""
"Tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desitassa viññātā "
"dhammānudhammappaṭipanno puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "A person who practices in line with the teaching."

msgctxt "an5.195:5.8"
msgid "Kataññū katavedī puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "A person who is grateful and thankful."

msgctxt "an5.195:5.9"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ kho, licchavī, pañcannaṃ ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmin”ti."
msgstr "The appearance of these five treasures is rare in the world.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.195:5.10"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
